com.yahoo.memory

Class Buffer

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.yahoo.memory.Buffer
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    WritableBuffer

    public abstract class Buffer
extends Object
    Provides read-only, positional primitive and primitive array methods to any of the four resources mentioned at the package level.
    Author:
    Lee Rhodes

      • compareTo

        public abstract int compareTo(long thisOffsetBytes,
                              long thisLengthBytes,
                              Buffer that,
                              long thatOffsetBytes,
                              long thatLengthBytes)
        Compares the bytes of this Memory to that Memory. This uses absolute offsets not the start, position and end. Returns (this < that) ? -1 : (this > that) ? 1 : 0;. If all bytes are equal up to the shorter of the two lengths, the shorter length is considered to be less than the other.
        Parameters:
        thisOffsetBytes - the starting offset for this Memory
        thisLengthBytes - the length of the region to compare from this Memory
        that - the other Memory to compare with
        thatOffsetBytes - the starting offset for that Memory
        thatLengthBytes - the length of the region to compare from that Memory
        Returns:
        (this < that) ? -1 : (this > that) ? 1 : 0;
